```

Website prompts ensure consistent knowledge presentation.

---

# Website Knowledge

Website prompts should retrieve knowledge from:

- Website Information Architecture
- Content Strategy
- Page Standards
- User Journey
- Conversion Strategy
- Design System
- AI Content Strategy

When required, website prompts should also retrieve knowledge from:

- Brand
- Products
- PDMS
- Marketing
- SEO

The Website module remains the authoritative source for website structure and presentation.

---

# Website Responsibilities

Website prompts should ensure that Artificial Intelligence:

- Follows official page structures.
- Uses consistent website terminology.
- Applies approved design principles.
- Organises content logically.
- Supports customer understanding.
- Reinforces customer confidence.
- Maintains consistency across all webpages.

Website prompts organise knowledge rather than redefine it.

---

# Prompt Workflow

Every website prompt follows one consistent workflow.

```text
Website Objective
        │
        ▼
Retrieve Website Standards
        │
        ▼
Retrieve Business Knowledge
        │
        ▼
Assemble Website Context
        │
        ▼
Artificial Intelligence
        │
        ▼
Structured Website Content
```

Website standards should always be applied before content generation.

---

# Website Context Assembly

Website content should always be generated from complete website context.

Website context may include:

- Page Type
- Target Audience
- Customer Journey Stage
- Required Business Knowledge
- Related Pages
- Internal Linking
- SEO Requirements
- Conversion Goals
- Design Standards

Well-assembled context produces better website experiences.

---

# Website Context Hierarchy

When assembling website context, Artificial Intelligence should prioritise information in the following order:

1. Website Standards
2. Customer Journey
3. Business Knowledge
4. SEO Requirements
5. Conversion Objectives
6. Design Standards

Website standards always determine how knowledge is organised.

Business knowledge determines what should be communicated.

SEO improves discoverability.

Conversion supports customer decisions.

Design improves the customer experience.

---

# Website Validation

Before generating website content, Artificial Intelligence should confirm that:

- Website standards are being followed.
- Business knowledge is accurate.
- Information architecture is respected.
- Related pages are connected appropriately.
- Content supports the intended customer journey.
- Customer confidence is strengthened.

Website validation should occur before publication.

---

# Website Principles

Every website prompt should:

- Retrieve official website standards.
- Organise knowledge logically.
- Maintain consistent terminology.
- Support customer understanding.
- Strengthen customer confidence.
- Preserve information hierarchy.
- Improve discoverability.

Artificial Intelligence should never:

- Invent website structures.
- Ignore approved design standards.
- Duplicate existing knowledge.
- Break information architecture.

